  <h2><xar:mlstring>Overview</xar:mlstring></h2>

  <h3><xar:mlstring>What is it?</xar:mlstring></h3>
  <p>
    <em><xar:mlstring>XarDPLink is a utility module for Xaraya and DotProject.</xar:mlstring></em>
    <xar:mlstring>It is currently responsible for accomplishing two main tasks:</xar:mlstring>
  </p>
  <ol>
    <li><xar:mlstring>Provide a common login.</xar:mlstring></li>
    <li><xar:mlstring>More to come...</xar:mlstring></li>

  </ol>
  <h3><xar:mlstring>How to use it?</xar:mlstring></h3>
  <ul>
    <li><xar:mlstring>Please, first install DotProject (see their homepage at</xar:mlstring> <a href="http://www.dotproject.net">http://www.dotproject.net</a>)</li>


    <li><xar:mlstring>Then edit the configuration in DotProject to use the "Postnuke" authentication (a FR in Dotproject to use Xaraya there is on its way)</xar:mlstring></li>
    <li><xar:mlstring>Edit the config of this module</xar:mlstring></li>
    <li><xar:mlstring>Choose if you want to show a full new browserwindow when following the link, or to use the Window module.</xar:mlstring></li>
    <li><xar:mlstring>When you choose for the Window module, you will need to install it seperately. At installation of xarDPLink, there is no check for a dependency</xar:mlstring></li>
  </ul>
  <h3>
    <xar:mlstring>Further Information</xar:mlstring>
  </h3>
  <p>
    <xar:mlstring>Further information on this module can be found at</xar:mlstring>
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><xar:mlstring>the xarDPLink Extension page at</xar:mlstring> <a title="#xarML('xarDPLink Module - Xaraya Extension 591')#" href="http://www.xaraya.com/index.php/release/591.html">Xaraya Extension and Releases</a>.
      <xar:mlstring> Click on Version History tab at the bottom to get the latest release information.</xar:mlstring>
    </li>
    <li><xar:mlstring>Related tutorials and documentation on xarDPLink can be found at</xar:mlstring> <a href="http://www.xaraya.com/index.php/keywords/example/" title="#xarML('Related documentation on Example')#"><xar:mlstring>Xaraya Documentation.</xar:mlstring></a>
    </li>
  </ul>
